r%20ourselves.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EEven%20our%20drive%20to%20the%20region%20felt%20incredibly%20scenic.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Stones%2C%20grass%20in%20front%20of%20water%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68f286c31c1f80efbec5cfaa%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMira%20Miller%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20reach%20this%20region%2C%20my%20partner%20and%20I%20drove%20400%20miles%20outside%20the%20city%20along%20the%20south%20shore%20of%20the%20lower%20Saint%20Lawrence%20River%2C%20nicknamed%20%26quot%3BBas-du-Fleuve.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20in%20this%20area%20that%20the%20river%20widens%20into%20a%20gulf%20that%20flows%20into%20the%20Atlantic%20Ocean.%20The%20water%20is%20vast%20%E2%80%94%20a%20mix%20of%20fresh%20and%20saltwater%20%E2%80%94%20and%20breathtakingly%20beautiful.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drive%20from%20Montreal%20to%20Bas-du-Fleuve%20takes%20roughly%20six%20hours%20if%20you%20go%20straight%20and%20take%20the%20largest%20highway.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20a%20little%20longer%20if%20you%20opt%20for%20the%20slower%2C%20more%20scenic%20route%20and%20make%20stops%20along%20the%20way%20like%20we%20did.%20Trust%20me%2C%20it's%20worth%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20drive%20gets%20especially%20pretty%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fvisited-quebec-city-canada-european-inspired-trip-budget-2025-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EQuebec%20City%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20where%20the%20views%20of%20the%20water%20begin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20area%20is%20known%20for%20its%20fresh%20fish%2C%20local%20meats%20and%20cheeses%20(hello%2C%20cheese%20curds)%2C%20and%20craft%20beer.%20So%2C%20we%20made%20stops%20at%20T%C3%AAte%20d'Allumette%2C%20a%20microbrewery%20with%20a%20beautiful%20terrace%20overlooking%20the%20river%2C%20a%20smoked%20fish%20store%20called%20March%C3%A9%20Des%20Trois%20Fumoirs%2C%20and%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbest-cheese-shops-in-nyc-2013-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Especialty%20cheese%20store%3C%2Fa%3E%20called%20Fromagerie%20des%20Basques%20to%20stock%20up%20on%20local%20goodies.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20eventually%20arrived%20at%20Motel%20de%20la%20Mer%2C%20which%20looks%20out%20at%20the%20river%2C%20where%20we%20all%20stayed%20in%20an%20apartment-style%20accommodation.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWe%20found%20plenty%20to%20do%20in%20the%20area.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Exterior%20of%20a%20submarine%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68f2869d5dbc4fd10dab1288%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESubmarine%3Cp%3EMira%20Miller%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EOur%20first%20morning%20in%20Bas-Saint-Laurent%20was%20rainy%2C%20so%20we%20toured%20the%20Onondaga%2C%20a%20295-foot%20submarine%20that%20traversed%20the%20North%20Atlantic%20from%201967%20to%202000.%20It's%20also%20the%20first%20publicly%20accessible%20submarine%20in%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20also%20stopped%20next%20door%20to%20visit%20the%20Empress%20of%20Ireland%20Museum%2C%20an%20exhibition%20about%20the%20greatest%20maritime%20tragedy%20in%20Canadian%20history.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20we%20met%20up%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20gang%20for%20brunch%20in%20downtown%20Rimouski%2C%20the%20biggest%20city%20in%20the%20area.%20We%20filled%20up%20on%20eggs%2C%20crepes%2C%20bacon%2C%20and%20good%20coffee%20before%20walking%20around%20the%20city%20center%20and%20popping%20into%20cute%20local%20shops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EIt%20was%20especially%20wonderful%20to%20walk%20along%20the%20shore.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Shells%2C%20stones%2C%20in%20wet%20sand%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68f2869d1c1f80efbec5cf8e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMira%20Miller%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ELater%20that%20afternoon%2C%20at%20low%20tide%2C%20we%20walked%20along%20the%20nearby%20shore%2C%20taking%20in%20the%20views%20as%20we%20looked%20for%20interesting%20rocks%20and%20shells.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20tide%20is%20low%20in%20this%20region%2C%20parts%20of%20the%20shoreline%20become%20exposed%2C%20and%20you%20can%20actually%20see%20and%20explore%20the%20sea%20floor.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20tide%20rises%20again%2C%20that%20same%20shoreline%20is%20resubmerged.%20There%20are%20different%20high%20and%20low%20tides%20each%20day%2C%20and%20their%20timing%20and%20height%20vary.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWe%20also%20enjoyed%20having%20fresh%20seafood.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Seafood%20salad%20in%20plastic%20container%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68f287191c1f80efbec5cfb9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22720%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWe%20loved%20eating%20Fresh%20seafood%20with%20a%20Quebecois%20twist.%3Cp%3EMira%20Miller%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20evening%2C%20we%20picked%20up%20dinner%20from%20a%20casse-cro%C3%BBte%2C%20a%20locally%20used%20term%20for%20a%20small%2C%20casual%20establishment%20that%20serves%20comfort%20food.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20had%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Freview-best-lobster-roll-in-portland-maine-ranked-with-prices-2024-8%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Elobster%20roll%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20fries%20while%20my%20partner%20had%20a%20lobster%20poutine.%20%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWe%20were%20highly%20impressed%20with%20the%20quantity%20and%20freshness%20of%20the%20seafood.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EThe%20nearby%20provincial%20park%20is%20beautiful%20%E2%80%94%20but%20beware%20of%20the%20fickle%20weather.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Park%20with%20wildflowers%2C%20greenery%2C%20next%20to%20water%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68f2869d1c1f80efbec5cf90%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3Eprovincial%20park%3Cp%3EMira%20Miller%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20following%20day%2C%20we%20headed%20out%20to%20Parc%20national%20du%20Bic%2C%20a%20beautiful%20provincial%20park%20nearby.%20We%20had%20a%20picnic%20and%20then%20started%20walking%20along%20the%20shoreline%20before%20turning%20onto%20one%20of%20the%20many%20hiking%20trails%20in%20the%20woods.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20weather%20started%20off%20gray%20and%20cloudy%2C%20but%20eventually%20turned%20to%20heavy%20rainstorms%20that%20left%20us%20quite%20wet.%20We%20laughed%20it%20off%20and%20still%20had%20a%20good%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20region%20regularly%20experiences%20rainfall%20(in%20part%20due%20to%20the%20St.%20Lawrence's%20oceanic%20influence)%2C%20so%20be%20sure%20to%20pack%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fstyle%2Fbest-rain-jacket-women%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Egreat%20rain%20jacket%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20boots%20if%20you%20plan%20to%20visit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cdiv%3EWe%20also%20experienced%20the%20area's%20famous%20sunsets.%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221280%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Sunset%20over%20side%20of%20road%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F68f2869d1c1f80efbec5cf91%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22960%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cp%3EMira%20Miller%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spectacular%20sunsets%20alone%20are%20reason%20enough%20to%20visit%20Bas-du-Fleuve.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESome%20even%20refer%20to%20the%20region%20as%20%26quot%3Bthe%20capital%20of%20sunsets%26quot%3B%20for%20its%20western-facing%20vantage%20point%20combined%20with%20the%20beauty%20of%20the%20river%2C%20which%20makes%20for%20stunning%20sundown%20sights%20most%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%3